================================================================================
THIRD-PARTY DATA SOURCES (FOR ENRICHMENT AT RUNTIME)
================================================================================

This project uses metadata fetched from the following open scholarly
infrastructure services. We acknowledge and credit each source:

* OpenAlex — https://openalex.org/
  Bibliographic metadata for papers, authors, institutions, and concepts.
  Data dedicated to the public domain (CC0 1.0).
  Citation: Priem, J., Piwowar, H., & Orr, R. (2022). OpenAlex: A
  fully-open index of scholarly works, authors, venues, institutions,
  and concepts. arXiv:2205.01833.

* ROR (Research Organization Registry) — https://ror.org/
  Persistent identifiers and metadata for research organizations.
  Released under CC0 1.0.

* ORCID — https://orcid.org/
  Persistent identifiers for researchers and public profile data,
  released by ORCID under CC0 for the public data file. Individual
  ORCID record content is published under the terms chosen by the
  record holder; respect each researcher's privacy settings.

* OpenAIRE — https://www.openaire.eu/
  Metadata about research projects, software, datasets, and funding.
  Most metadata is released under CC BY or CC0; check per-record terms.

* Wikidata — https://www.wikidata.org/
  Structured open knowledge base. Data licensed under CC0 1.0.

* ORKG (Open Research Knowledge Graph) — https://orkg.org/
  Structured descriptions and comparisons of research contributions.
  Most content licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0 unless stated otherwise.

